Mukwevho started with the utility in 2003 as a depot manager. In 2006 he joined the investment delivery department as a divisional manager, where, over the following three years, he was involved in the construction of a number of projects at the Northern and Driefontein Wastewater Treatment Works. Later in 2009, Mukwevho joined the capital investment and infrastructure development department as general manager. Following his appointment as chief operations officer in 2012, Mukwevho has focused on the development and co-ordination of comprehensive strategies and implementation plans driven by the strategic vision of the City of Joburg.